  user_input {
    user_response: "Using the attached wireframe image as a structural reference, design a modern, production-ready **single-page teacher assistant web application** built with **React + Vite**.\n\nThe visual style should be heavily inspired by modern AI chatbot interfaces such as:\n\n* ChatGPT\n* Claude (Anthropic)\n* Perplexity\n* Notion AI\n\nThe result should feel clean, professional, highly scalable, and optimized for daily teacher workflows.\n\n---\n\n# Application Purpose\n\nThis application is a **Teacher Assistant Platform**.\n\nIts purpose is to help teachers:\n\n* Track student performance\n* Analyze answer sheets\n* Monitor progress and learning gaps\n* Compare students across assessments\n* Generate insights using RAG (Retrieval Augmented Generation)\n* Organize class materials\n* Manage student information\n* Build reusable teaching templates\n\nThe system should be designed around a workspace model similar to AI chatbot applications.\n\n---\n\n# Design Goals\n\nDesign a UI that is:\n\n* Modern\n* Minimal\n* AI-first\n* Workspace-centric\n* Highly responsive\n* Accessible\n* Mobile friendly\n* Keyboard navigable\n* Dark mode ready\n* Suitable for large datasets\n\nThe interface should feel like a combination of:\n\n* ChatGPT workspace\n* Claude project workspace\n* Notion database views\n* Airtable organization patterns\n\n---\n\n# Layout Requirements\n\nUse the attached image as a conceptual layout reference.\n\nThe application must remain a **single page application**.\n\nNo full-page navigations should occur.\n\nEverything should happen inside the SPA.\n\n---\n\n# Global Layout\n\n## Left Sidebar\n\nPersistent sidebar similar to ChatGPT.\n\nContains:\n\n### Templates Section\n\nReusable teacher templates.\n\nExamples:\n\n* Grade 10 Mathematics\n* Physics Practical Analysis\n* Exam Evaluation Template\n* Custom Teaching Style Template\n\nFunctions:\n\n* Create\n* Rename\n* Duplicate\n* Delete\n* Save current workspace as template\n\n---\n\n### Workspace Projects\n\nList of workspaces.\n\nExamples:\n\n* Grade 10 Mathematics\n* Grade 9 Physics\n* Chemistry Semester 1\n\nFunctions:\n\n* Create workspace\n* Rename\n* Duplicate\n* Archive\n* Delete\n\n---\n\n### Account Controls\n\nBottom section:\n\n* Profile\n* Preferences\n* Settings\n* Subscription\n* Theme\n* Logout\n\nAll open as modals.\n\n---\n\n# Workspace Layout\n\nWorkspace consists of three major areas.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Details Section\n\nLocated at top-left of workspace.\n\nContains:\n\n### Class Information\n\n* Class name\n* Subject\n* Academic year\n* Semester\n* Teacher\n\n### Teaching Information\n\n* Teaching style\n* Experience level\n* Special notes\n* Assessment preferences\n\n### Learning Material Repository\n\nTeacher can upload:\n\n* PDFs\n* Books\n* Text documents\n* Notes\n* Question papers\n* Syllabus documents\n* Recommended reading materials\n\nDisplay:\n\n* File cards\n* Metadata\n* Upload date\n* Tags\n\nFunctions:\n\n* Add\n* Edit\n* Delete\n* Version history\n\n---\n\n### Reusable Instructions\n\nTeacher can define:\n\n* Global prompts\n* Subject prompts\n* Marking instructions\n* Evaluation criteria\n* Classroom preferences\n\nThese should be reusable across workspaces.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Student Section\n\nLocated top-right of workspace.\n\nDisplay students as horizontally scrollable cards/tabs.\n\nEach student card contains:\n\n* Name\n* Profile picture\n* Performance indicator\n* Status indicator\n\n---\n\n### Student Data\n\nEach student supports:\n\n#### Basic Information\n\n* Name\n* Roll number\n* Email\n* Phone\n* Address\n\n#### Parent Information\n\n* Parent names\n* Contacts\n* Notes\n\n#### Academic Records\n\n* Grades\n* Assignments\n* Projects\n* Attendance\n\n#### Uploads\n\n* Answer sheets\n* Homework\n* Project submissions\n* Feedback forms\n\n---\n\n### Custom Fields\n\nSupport unlimited custom fields similar to Google Contacts.\n\nExamples:\n\n* Learning disability\n* Tutoring status\n* Language proficiency\n* Counselor notes\n* Custom tags\n\nTeacher can define:\n\n* Field type\n* Validation\n* Visibility\n\n---\n\n## 3. RAG Workspace\n\nMain analysis area.\n\nLargest section of the interface.\n\nThis is the primary AI interaction area.\n\n---\n\n# RAG Sessions\n\nSimilar to ChatGPT conversations.\n\nLeft panel inside RAG workspace contains:\n\n* New Analysis\n* Existing Analyses\n\nExamples:\n\n* Midterm Analysis\n* Weak Students Review\n* Grade Prediction\n* Parent Meeting Summary\n\nEach session supports:\n\n* Rename\n* Duplicate\n* Delete\n* Archive\n\nImportant:\n\nDeleting a RAG session must NOT delete:\n\n* Student records\n* Uploaded materials\n* Analytics datasets\n\nSessions only represent conversations and analysis contexts.\n\n---\n\n# New Analysis Workflow\n\nWhen user clicks:\n\n\"New Analysis\"\n\nShow modal allowing:\n\n### Analysis Type\n\nExamples:\n\n* Student Performance Analysis\n* Class Strength Analysis\n* Weak Topic Detection\n* Question Paper Analysis\n* Learning Gap Analysis\n* Parent Report Generation\n* Custom Analysis\n\n---\n\n### Analysis Scope\n\nSelect:\n\n* Entire class\n* Selected students\n* Selected assessments\n* Uploaded materials\n\n---\n\n### Instructions\n\nOptional custom instructions.\n\n---\n\nAfter creation:\n\nOpen a chatbot-style interface.\n\n---\n\n# Chat Interface\n\nDesign similar to ChatGPT.\n\nIncludes:\n\n### Chat History\n\nScrollable messages.\n\n### Input Area\n\nSupports:\n\n* Text\n* Attachments\n* Prompt suggestions\n\n### Analysis Panels\n\nMessages can render:\n\n* Charts\n* Graphs\n* Tables\n* Student rankings\n* Heatmaps\n* Progress timelines\n\n---\n\n# Focus Mode\n\nWhen user enters an active RAG session:\n\nAutomatically maximize the chat area.\n\nHide:\n\n* Details section\n* Student section\n\nDisplay:\n\n* Back to Workspace button\n\nThis should feel similar to entering a conversation in ChatGPT.\n\n---\n\n# Modal System\n\nAll secondary functionality should use modals.\n\nExamples:\n\n### Account Modals\n\n* Settings\n* Preferences\n* Profile\n* Subscription\n\n### Workspace Modals\n\n* Edit Class\n* Edit Teacher\n* Add Material\n* Edit Student\n* Upload Answer Sheet\n* Create Template\n* Create Analysis\n\nRequirements:\n\n* Centered modal\n* Rounded corners\n* Smooth animation\n* Dark translucent backdrop\n* Background blur\n* ESC key closes modal\n* Click outside closes modal\n* Accessible focus trapping\n\n---\n\n# Analytics Dashboard Requirements\n\nThe RAG workspace should support future analytics components such as:\n\n### Student Metrics\n\n* Performance trends\n* Topic mastery\n* Weakness detection\n* Improvement velocity\n\n### Class Metrics\n\n* Average scores\n* Distribution charts\n* Difficulty analysis\n\n### AI Insights\n\n* Suggested interventions\n* Personalized recommendations\n* Predicted outcomes\n\n### Visualization Components\n\n* Bar charts\n* Radar charts\n* Heatmaps\n* Timelines\n* Scatter plots\n* Comparative tables\n\n---\n\n# UX Requirements\n\nImplement:\n\n* Command palette\n* Global search\n* Keyboard shortcuts\n* Drag-and-drop uploads\n* Persistent autosave\n* Toast notifications\n* Context menus\n* Breadcrumbs\n* Empty states\n* Loading skeletons\n\n---\n\n# Technical Frontend Requirements\n\nGenerate:\n\n1. Complete UI architecture\n2. Component hierarchy\n3. React + Vite folder structure\n4. State management approach\n5. Modal management strategy\n6. Workspace data model\n7. Student data model\n8. Template data model\n9. RAG session data model\n10. Responsive layout behavior\n11. Dark/light theme design\n12. Recommended component library\n13. Recommended charting library\n14. Design token system\n15. Accessibility considerations\n\n---\n\n# Output Format\n\nProvide:\n\n1. Product architecture\n2. Information architecture\n3. User flows\n4. Screen hierarchy\n5. Component hierarchy\n6. React component breakdown\n7. Suggested folder structure\n8. Design system specification\n9. UI behavior descriptions\n10. Responsive behavior\n11. Future scalability considerations\n\nUse the attached wireframe image as the primary structural reference while improving the layout where necessary according to modern AI workspace UX standards.\n\nif there are any confusions or additional questions. ask me before making any major architectural assumptions."
    items {
      text: "Using the attached wireframe image as a structural reference, design a modern, production-ready **single-page teacher assistant web application** built with **React + Vite**.\n\nThe visual style should be heavily inspired by modern AI chatbot interfaces such as:\n\n* ChatGPT\n* Claude (Anthropic)\n* Perplexity\n* Notion AI\n\nThe result should feel clean, professional, highly scalable, and optimized for daily teacher workflows.\n\n---\n\n# Application Purpose\n\nThis application is a **Teacher Assistant Platform**.\n\nIts purpose is to help teachers:\n\n* Track student performance\n* Analyze answer sheets\n* Monitor progress and learning gaps\n* Compare students across assessments\n* Generate insights using RAG (Retrieval Augmented Generation)\n* Organize class materials\n* Manage student information\n* Build reusable teaching templates\n\nThe system should be designed around a workspace model similar to AI chatbot applications.\n\n---\n\n# Design Goals\n\nDesign a UI that is:\n\n* Modern\n* Minimal\n* AI-first\n* Workspace-centric\n* Highly responsive\n* Accessible\n* Mobile friendly\n* Keyboard navigable\n* Dark mode ready\n* Suitable for large datasets\n\nThe interface should feel like a combination of:\n\n* ChatGPT workspace\n* Claude project workspace\n* Notion database views\n* Airtable organization patterns\n\n---\n\n# Layout Requirements\n\nUse the attached image as a conceptual layout reference.\n\nThe application must remain a **single page application**.\n\nNo full-page navigations should occur.\n\nEverything should happen inside the SPA.\n\n---\n\n# Global Layout\n\n## Left Sidebar\n\nPersistent sidebar similar to ChatGPT.\n\nContains:\n\n### Templates Section\n\nReusable teacher templates.\n\nExamples:\n\n* Grade 10 Mathematics\n* Physics Practical Analysis\n* Exam Evaluation Template\n* Custom Teaching Style Template\n\nFunctions:\n\n* Create\n* Rename\n* Duplicate\n* Delete\n* Save current workspace as template\n\n---\n\n### Workspace Projects\n\nList of workspaces.\n\nExamples:\n\n* Grade 10 Mathematics\n* Grade 9 Physics\n* Chemistry Semester 1\n\nFunctions:\n\n* Create workspace\n* Rename\n* Duplicate\n* Archive\n* Delete\n\n---\n\n### Account Controls\n\nBottom section:\n\n* Profile\n* Preferences\n* Settings\n* Subscription\n* Theme\n* Logout\n\nAll open as modals.\n\n---\n\n# Workspace Layout\n\nWorkspace consists of three major areas.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Details Section\n\nLocated at top-left of workspace.\n\nContains:\n\n### Class Information\n\n* Class name\n* Subject\n* Academic year\n* Semester\n* Teacher\n\n### Teaching Information\n\n* Teaching style\n* Experience level\n* Special notes\n* Assessment preferences\n\n### Learning Material Repository\n\nTeacher can upload:\n\n* PDFs\n* Books\n* Text documents\n* Notes\n* Question papers\n* Syllabus documents\n* Recommended reading materials\n\nDisplay:\n\n* File cards\n* Metadata\n* Upload date\n* Tags\n\nFunctions:\n\n* Add\n* Edit\n* Delete\n* Version history\n\n---\n\n### Reusable Instructions\n\nTeacher can define:\n\n* Global prompts\n* Subject prompts\n* Marking instructions\n* Evaluation criteria\n* Classroom preferences\n\nThese should be reusable across workspaces.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Student Section\n\nLocated top-right of workspace.\n\nDisplay students as horizontally scrollable cards/tabs.\n\nEach student card contains:\n\n* Name\n* Profile picture\n* Performance indicator\n* Status indicator\n\n---\n\n### Student Data\n\nEach student supports:\n\n#### Basic Information\n\n* Name\n* Roll number\n* Email\n* Phone\n* Address\n\n#### Parent Information\n\n* Parent names\n* Contacts\n* Notes\n\n#### Academic Records\n\n* Grades\n* Assignments\n* Projects\n* Attendance\n\n#### Uploads\n\n* Answer sheets\n* Homework\n* Project submissions\n* Feedback forms\n\n---\n\n### Custom Fields\n\nSupport unlimited custom fields similar to Google Contacts.\n\nExamples:\n\n* Learning disability\n* Tutoring status\n* Language proficiency\n* Counselor notes\n* Custom tags\n\nTeacher can define:\n\n* Field type\n* Validation\n* Visibility\n\n---\n\n## 3. RAG Workspace\n\nMain analysis area.\n\nLargest section of the interface.\n\nThis is the primary AI interaction area.\n\n---\n\n# RAG Sessions\n\nSimilar to ChatGPT conversations.\n\nLeft panel inside RAG workspace contains:\n\n* New Analysis\n* Existing Analyses\n\nExamples:\n\n* Midterm Analysis\n* Weak Students Review\n* Grade Prediction\n* Parent Meeting Summary\n\nEach session supports:\n\n* Rename\n* Duplicate\n* Delete\n* Archive\n\nImportant:\n\nDeleting a RAG session must NOT delete:\n\n* Student records\n* Uploaded materials\n* Analytics datasets\n\nSessions only represent conversations and analysis contexts.\n\n---\n\n# New Analysis Workflow\n\nWhen user clicks:\n\n\"New Analysis\"\n\nShow modal allowing:\n\n### Analysis Type\n\nExamples:\n\n* Student Performance Analysis\n* Class Strength Analysis\n* Weak Topic Detection\n* Question Paper Analysis\n* Learning Gap Analysis\n* Parent Report Generation\n* Custom Analysis\n\n---\n\n### Analysis Scope\n\nSelect:\n\n* Entire class\n* Selected students\n* Selected assessments\n* Uploaded materials\n\n---\n\n### Instructions\n\nOptional custom instructions.\n\n---\n\nAfter creation:\n\nOpen a chatbot-style interface.\n\n---\n\n# Chat Interface\n\nDesign similar to ChatGPT.\n\nIncludes:\n\n### Chat History\n\nScrollable messages.\n\n### Input Area\n\nSupports:\n\n* Text\n* Attachments\n* Prompt suggestions\n\n### Analysis Panels\n\nMessages can render:\n\n* Charts\n* Graphs\n* Tables\n* Student rankings\n* Heatmaps\n* Progress timelines\n\n---\n\n# Focus Mode\n\nWhen user enters an active RAG session:\n\nAutomatically maximize the chat area.\n\nHide:\n\n* Details section\n* Student section\n\nDisplay:\n\n* Back to Workspace button\n\nThis should feel similar to entering a conversation in ChatGPT.\n\n---\n\n# Modal System\n\nAll secondary functionality should use modals.\n\nExamples:\n\n### Account Modals\n\n* Settings\n* Preferences\n* Profile\n* Subscription\n\n### Workspace Modals\n\n* Edit Class\n* Edit Teacher\n* Add Material\n* Edit Student\n* Upload Answer Sheet\n* Create Template\n* Create Analysis\n\nRequirements:\n\n* Centered modal\n* Rounded corners\n* Smooth animation\n* Dark translucent backdrop\n* Background blur\n* ESC key closes modal\n* Click outside closes modal\n* Accessible focus trapping\n\n---\n\n# Analytics Dashboard Requirements\n\nThe RAG workspace should support future analytics components such as:\n\n### Student Metrics\n\n* Performance trends\n* Topic mastery\n* Weakness detection\n* Improvement velocity\n\n### Class Metrics\n\n* Average scores\n* Distribution charts\n* Difficulty analysis\n\n### AI Insights\n\n* Suggested interventions\n* Personalized recommendations\n* Predicted outcomes\n\n### Visualization Components\n\n* Bar charts\n* Radar charts\n* Heatmaps\n* Timelines\n* Scatter plots\n* Comparative tables\n\n---\n\n# UX Requirements\n\nImplement:\n\n* Command palette\n* Global search\n* Keyboard shortcuts\n* Drag-and-drop uploads\n* Persistent autosave\n* Toast notifications\n* Context menus\n* Breadcrumbs\n* Empty states\n* Loading skeletons\n\n---\n\n# Technical Frontend Requirements\n\nGenerate:\n\n1. Complete UI architecture\n2. Component hierarchy\n3. React + Vite folder structure\n4. State management approach\n5. Modal management strategy\n6. Workspace data model\n7. Student data model\n8. Template data model\n9. RAG session data model\n10. Responsive layout behavior\n11. Dark/light theme design\n12. Recommended component library\n13. Recommended charting library\n14. Design token system\n15. Accessibility considerations\n\n---\n\n# Output Format\n\nProvide:\n\n1. Product architecture\n2. Information architecture\n3. User flows\n4. Screen hierarchy\n5. Component hierarchy\n6. React component breakdown\n7. Suggested folder structure\n8. Design system specification\n9. UI behavior descriptions\n10. Responsive behavior\n11. Future scalability considerations\n\nUse the attached wireframe image as the primary structural reference while improving the layout where necessary according to modern AI workspace UX standards.\n\nif there are any confusions or additional questions. ask me before making any major architectural assumptions."
    }
