  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining the Stack**\n\nI\'ve clarified the stack; it\'s definitely full-stack! The template confirms this with Express, TSX, and React + Express + Vite guidelines. The Gemini API key will stay server-side, securing the `server.ts` file.\n\n\n**Inspecting the File Structure**\n\nI\'m now diving into the file structure. I\'m focusing on `package.json` to ensure the scripts align with the Express + Vite setup. I\'ve also spotted some `.gitignore` files to ensure proper version control. Furthermore, I\'ll update `metadata.json` for name and description, starting with \"untitled apps\".\n\n\n**Designing the Workspace**\n\nI\'m now designing the data model and workspace structure for \"Teacher Assistant Workspace\". I\'m prioritizing the backend. The absence of `server.ts` means I need to create the full-stack Express server to handle API calls, including Gemini chat, simulated grading, and student/material analysis. I also confirmed standard `lucide-react` is present.\n\n\n**Outlining Workspace Components**\n\nI\'m currently outlining the workspace, specifically the left sidebar and its sections. I\'m focusing on the \"Templates Section,\" \"Workspace Projects,\" and \"Account Controls.\" I\'ve specified functionalities such as create, rename, duplicate, archive and delete. I\'m also planning the \"Workspace Layout,\" detailing sections for class details, teaching information, and the material repository. I\'m sketching out the details and reusable instructions.\n\n\n**Defining Student Section**\n\nI\'m now detailing the student section, envisioning horizontally scrollable cards with key indicators and information. I\'m focusing on the data structure, including basic student info, academic records, and custom fields mimicking Google Contacts. I\'m prioritizing user experience with a focus on ease of navigation and quick access to essential data points.\n\n**Structuring the RAG Workspace**\n\nI\'m now outlining the RAG workspace. I\'m structuring RAG sessions similar to ChatGPT chats, to manage different analyses. I\'m focusing on \"New Analysis Workflow,\" where the user can choose how to initiate each analysis. Importantly, deleting a RAG session won\'t affect the student or material data.\n\n\n**Detailing the Analytics**\n\nI\'m now detailing the RAG analysis types, including Student Performance, Class Strength, and Weak Topic Detection, with varying scopes. I\'m prioritizing the chat interface and envisioning scrollable messages, analysis panels that render diverse visualizations, and a \"Focus Mode\" for distraction-free analysis. I\'m also planning rounded modals and an analytics dashboard with charts and tables. I\'m outlining UX features like command palettes and keyboard shortcuts. Finally, I\'m noting the tech frontend requirements.\n\n\n**Building the Foundation**\n\nI\'m now focusing on ensuring a modular structure for the workspace, aiming for an interactive and visually appealing design. I\'m reviewing existing dependencies like `@google/genai`, `express`, and `dotenv`, and identifying the need for `recharts` for data visualization. I\'m verifying the compatibility of `recharts` with the React version and noting it can be installed with `install_applet_package`.\n\n\n**Defining Data Types**\n\nI\'m now defining the data types for the workspace. The plan is to create `/src/types.ts` first. I\'ve defined the `Workspace` data type, including `id`, `name`, `classInfo` (with class details), `teachingStyle`, and `experience` as attributes.\n\n\n**Structuring Data Types**\n\nI\'m now detailing the remaining data types. I\'ve defined `Material`, with fields like `id`, `name`, and `type`, and `Instruction` which has `id`, `title`, and `type` fields. Additionally, `Student` has `id`, `name`, and other details, while `CustomField`, `Grade`, and `StudentUpload` are also outlined.\n\n\n**Defining RAG Session Types**\n\nI\'m now detailing the `RAGSession` and `Message` data types, and adding them to `/src/types.ts`. I\'m specifying a `scopeType` with options like \"class\", \"students\", \"materials\", and \"assessments.\" For each `RAGSession`, I\'ll include attributes such as `id`, `title`, and `customInstructions`, along with an array of `messages` and an `archived` flag. Each `Message` will encompass details like `role`, `text`, `timestamp`, and attachments.\n\n\n"
