  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Constructing Server Implementation**\n\nI\'m now focusing on building the `server.ts` file. The goal is a full-stack server incorporating an Express instance. This will involve importing `express`, `path`, `createViteServer` from `vite`, and the `@google/genai` library, specifically the `GoogleGenAI` object. I am working on the initial architecture of the server and its integrations.\n\n\n**Implementing Chart Visualizations**\n\nI\'ve made progress on the `/api/chat` route, leveraging Gemini 3.5-flash. I\'ve confirmed we can instruct the AI to generate markdown-formatted responses *including* JSON payloads for chart visualization. This JSON will include `text` for the analysis and a `visualization` object specifying the chart type (charts, heatmap, etc.) and data. I\'m incorporating detailed instructions for the Gemini API call, focusing on key configurations such as the API key, user agent, the `generateContent` method, and avoiding `response.text()`.\n\n\n**Adding Body Parser**\n\nI\'ve added the standard Express body parser to `server.ts`, with a 10MB limit. I\'m focusing now on the `/api/chat` route, defining the expected request body structure, including  `messages`, `workspaceName`, `subject`, `classInfo`, `instructions`, `materials`, `students`, `customPrompt`, `analysisType`, and `scope`. My current thinking is on constructing a robust system instruction for Gemini, framing it as a Senior AI Pedagogical Consultant and Expert Teacher Assistant, aimed at automating feedback, diagnosing instruction gaps, and analyzing exams.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create the `/server.ts` entry point, implementing our custom Express API backend. This file serves the server-side Gemini RAG proxy under `/api/chat` (complete with class RAG context bundling and automatic dynamic visualization generation) and integrates the Vite middleware for development while supporting static serving in production."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 5
      nanos: 455274530
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
