    thinking: "**Modeling the React App**\n\nI\'m now diving into the React application\'s architecture. I\'ve decided to break it down into highly cohesive components for better maintainability. First up, `/src/components/Sidebar.tsx` will house the left sidebar, containing the header with logo/description, and a reusable templates section with create, rename, duplicate, delete, and save actions.\n\n\n**Defining Workspace UI Components**\n\nI\'m now detailing the application\'s workspace interface. I\'m focusing on three primary components: the workspace list and account controls in `Sidebar.tsx`, the workspace details panel in `WorkspaceDetails.tsx`, and the student register in `StudentRegister.tsx`. I\'m breaking these components down into specific features to allow full control of all workspace features.\n\n\n**Constructing RAG Workspace**\n\nI\'m now deeply engrossed in building `/src/components/RAGWorkspace.tsx`. The RAG Sessions sidebar tree is taking shape, along with the \"New Analysis\" button. I\'m focusing on the AI Chatbot Interface, and its ability to render user/assistant messages with markdown text and some very customized, animated visualizations to really give the app some character. I\'m aiming for stunning SVG/Tailwind grids for heatmaps, rankings, timelines, and stats. Plus, the modal system controller!\n\n\n**Building the Modular System**\n\nI\'m now building the modular components, starting with `/src/components/`, which I\'ll build first! I\'m planning out blurred modals for account settings, custom student fields, class settings, and material cards, and for analysis instantiation and worksheet creation. I\'ve also planned a Command Palette and Toast manager to create an intuitive and responsive experience.\n\n\n**Refining UX Components**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on UI refinements, starting with the modal system in `ModalSystem.tsx`, making it fully reusable by accepting `isOpen`, `onClose`, `title`, and `children`. I\'ve decided to include custom modals and toast system support using `Toast.tsx`. I think a local-state toast manager in `App.tsx` could make it highly reliable! I\'m planning to render the toast component directly there. I\'m now writing the React components in `/src/components/`, starting with `Sidebar`, `WorkspaceDetails`, `StudentRegister`, `RAGWorkspace`, and `CommandPalette`!\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create `/src/components/Sidebar.tsx`, the ChatGPT-style left sidebar component. It features templates management, customizable active workspaces list, archive toggle, search filters, and account modals triggers."
    thinking_duration {
