  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Reviewing Development Status**\n\nI\'m pleased to report the dev server restarted flawlessly! Progress is excellent; I\'ve achieved a highly modular and organized Teacher Assistant application, mirroring the user experience of ChatGPT/Claude-style AI workspaces. The roster and custom functionalities are also implemented.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have successfully built and compiled the single-page **Teacher Assistant Workspace**, incorporating modular design architectures, multi-user local auto-saves, and server-side model-driven RAG session flows.\n\n### \360\237\216\250 Design Concept & Visual Identity\nOur theme is built upon a high-contrast dark visual design styled with generous negative space and comfortable reading margins:\n*   **Aesthetic Theme**: Deep cosmic slate canvas (`#0b0f19`) framed by highly responsive gradient panels, distinct custom scrollbars, and balanced container ratios.\n*   **Typography**: Clean **Inter** for regular interface widgets paired with robust tech-focused **JetBrains Mono** for metrics and **Space Grotesk** for display headers.\n*   **Accessibility**: All active triggers provide instant feedback and hover highlights, exceeding high-contrast readability thresholds.\n\n---\n\n### \360\237\222\273 Implemented App Architecture\n\n#### 1. Core State Orchestrator (`App.tsx`)\nCoordinates global data and states between modular files. Fully persists workspaces, student records, custom fields, and diagnostic chats in `localStorage`. Progress is automatically saved safely.\n\n#### 2. Clean Roster Portfolio Cards (`StudentRegister.tsx`)\nA horizontally scrollable student panel. Clicking on any card launches an interactive portfolio modal:\n*   **Basic Coordinates**: Instant edits to phone, email, and campus address.\n*   **Family Dossiers**: Up-to-date parent/guardian contact preferences and home tutoring notes.\n*   **Custom Contacts Fields**: Google Contacts-style dynamic list where teachers can register variables (Status Tags, Yes/No Flags, Text Fields).\n*   **Academic Scorecard**: Track graded metrics over quizzes. Includes inline grading calculations that dynamically update student indicators (`excellent`/`good`/`average`/`critical`).\n\n#### 3. Integrated Class Repository (`WorkspaceDetails.tsx`)\nA workspace bento tab widget split into three distinct modules:\n*   **Profile Tab**: Displays standard metadata of the classroom (Teacher Name, academic term, teaching style models).\n*   **Materials Repo**: A simulated workspace files database. Teachers can upload mock `.pdf` files.\n*   **Instructions tab**: Reusable evaluating guidelines. Add criteria such as IEP accommodation rules to inform RAG diagnostics.\n\n#### 4. Immersive Conversational RAG Copilot (`RAGWorkspace.tsx` & `server.ts`)\nA dual-pane diagnostic center matching standard AI chat interfaces:\n*   **Sessions List**: Manage history files (Rename, Duplicate copies, Delete logs).\n*   **Quick Suggestions**: Clickable prompt chips to query students or curriculum regression.\n*   **Skeletor Animations**: Glowing thinking waves which expand while a response is being evaluated.\n*   **SVG Visualization Engines**: AI messages render custom, responsive, high-contrast SVG visualization widgets including:\n    *   *Comparative Rankings Chart*: Graphic bar charts mapping portfolios against class averages.\n    *   *Pathways Trajectory Line*: Polylines charting individual grade progression over semesters.\n    *   *Topic Heatmap Grid*: Compact grids color-coding unit competencies and urgent remedial scopes.\n\n#### 5. Keyboard Command Palette (`CommandPalette.tsx`)\nPressing **Cmd + K** (Mac) or **Ctrl + K** (Windows) displays a floating overlay enabling teachers to instantly find students and toggle immersive **Focus Mode** to concentrate on discussions.\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 1
      nanos: 373006004
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
