  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Assessing User\'s Intent**\n\nI\'m currently focused on dissecting the user\'s initial prompt. It appears they are seeking my opinion on using FastAPI for the backend, even though they\'re not asking for implementation. I\'m carefully noting the nuances of this request, which seems to imply an interest in architectural choices.\n\n\n**Clarifying Informational Needs**\n\nI\'m now identifying the user\'s information needs more precisely. It\'s an informational question, specifically seeking conceptual and architectural understanding, along with feature documentation, not code changes. The request is about determining the origin of workspace population and a comprehensive list of the app\'s features and actions, assuming backend AI features are implemented. This follows successful linting and compilation after addressing tailwind configuration in `src/index.css`.\n\n\n**Formulating Feature Bullets**\n\nNow I\'m creating a clear bulleted list of features and actions, as the user requested. I am aiming for a high-level overview, keeping it easily scannable and focusing on providing a well-proportioned view of the application\'s capabilities. It\'s meant to be descriptive and useful, but not a full feature dump.\n\n\n**Listing Key Features**\n\nI am now enumerating the core features and actionable workflows, starting from the details of Swagger documentation for client API call debugging. I\'ve noted that workspace data originates from a local default dataset initially, and then persists in the browser\'s local storage for user modifications and chat histories. Furthermore, assuming full backend AI integration, I am documenting capabilities like contextual classroom workspaces, custom prompting rubrics, and a roster/student portfolio tracker.\n\n\n**Detailing Actionable Workflows**\n\nI\'m expanding on the core features, focusing on actionable workflows within the AI-powered workspace. This includes multi-turn analyses with target focuses like learning gap analysis and interactive visual aids. I\'m also including detailed actions like workspace creation with templates and custom sections, along with actions for material registry and student portfolio management. I\'m aiming for comprehensiveness with a concise and actionable approach.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "### FastAPI for the Backend\nFastAPI is an **excellent choice** for an AI-powered educational application like this. Here is why it fits so well:\n* **AI & Python Integration**: Since most data science, document parsing (PDFs/scanners), and heavy RAG orchestration libraries (such as LangChain, LlamaIndex, and the Gemini Python SDK) live in Python, FastAPI allows you to write clean, native pythonic endpoints without needing a bridge layer.\n* **High Performance**: It leverages Python\'s `async/await` syntax and is built atop Starlette, making it incredibly fast. This is crucial when streaming conversational tokens or running asynchronous file indexing workflows in the background.\n* **Automatic Interactive API Docs**: The automatic generate schemas (Swagger UI/ReDoc) make debugging frontend-to-backend payload bridges fast and seamless.\n\n---\n\n### Where the Workspaces Data is Populated From\nThe application uses a **hybrid persistent architecture**:\n1. **Initial Seed**: When you load the application for the exact first time, it seeds itself with a realistic default classroom dataset (including Grade 10 Math samples, pre-configured diagnostic files, custom IEP instructions, and mock student grades).\n2. **Local Persistence**: Any subsequent actions you take (e.g., renaming a workspace, adding a student profile, logging a new score, uploading written work, or initiating AI chats) are saved directly to your browser\'s **Local Storage**. If you refresh or close your browser, your entire workspace state is preserved and restored.\n\n---\n\n### Features and Actions Available Right Now\n\nAssuming a fully functional AI backend is connected, here is a complete breakdown of what the application is designed to do:\n\n#### \360\237\223\202 1. Contextual Classroom Workspaces\nA separate, modular structure for managing different class cohorts, courses, or periods.\n* **Create New Workspaces**: Initialize new classes using pre-coded curriculum templates (e.g., Grade 10 Math, Socratic Algebra) or general course rooms.\n* **Customize Class Outlines**: Update teachers\' styling preferences, academic year, semester, and pedagogical rules.\n* **Workspace Lifecycle**: Duplicate complex classes to quickly replicate curriculum material, rename profiles, or archive contexts to keep the sidebar clean.\n* **Save as reusable templates**: Turn a highly customized classroom workspace into a template preset for future cohorts.\n\n#### \360\237\221\245 2. Student Portfolios & Roster registry\nA clinical scorecard dossier for tracking each student\'s academic and behavioral indicators.\n* **Roster Management**: Register new students, assign roll numbers, or remove student folders entirely.\n* **Profile Coordinates**: Track and update contact records (emails, contact preferences) and guardian/family instructions (such as priority tutoring guidelines).\n* **Flexible Custom Fields**: Create bespoke field parameters (such as *IEP Accommodation flags*, *Tutoring status indicator*, and *Remedial priority categories*).\n* **Live Scorecards**: Submit graded raw evaluations (e.g., Quiz 2 Polynomials, 85/100) along with custom qualitative teacher comments. The application automatically re-calculates average percentile performance brackets under the hood.\n* **Answer Sheet Logs**: Acknowledge, index, and manage static student submissions (like scanned homework sheets or midterm drafts).\n\n#### \360\237\244\226 3. Deep Conversational RAG Workspace\nThe focal point of instructional decision-making, designed around immersion and conversational depth.\n* **Multi-Turn Chat Dialogues**: Engage in conversational Q&A focusing on educational guidelines and student portfolios in real-time.\n* **Targeted Diagnostic Initializations**: Launch focused chat sessions designed around specialized target analysis options (e.g., *Weak Topic Detection*, *Learning Gap Analysis*, or *Parent Report Generation*).\n* **Multi-Scope Bounds Matching**: Tell the AI to scope its memory to **the entire class, selected students only, uploaded lesson materials, or scored grades databases**.\n* **Visual Data Widgets (Pure SVG Renderers)**: The AI returns interactive data visualizations that live as rich elements inside the chat bubble depending on the topic:\n  * **Mastery Heatmaps**: Visualizes topical secure and developing thresholds across specific parameters.\n  * **Score Trajectories**: An interactive coordinate pathway graph highlighting trends or regression curves over time.\n  * **Cohort Performance Rankings**: A scannable bar visualizer highlighting average mastery performance parameters alongside class thresholds.\n  * **Diagnostic Stats Cards**: Grid layouts compiling metrics, streak logs, or general demographic analytics cards.\n\n#### \342\232\241 4. Distraction-Free Focus & Command Palette\nDesigned to feel like advanced productivity utilities (Notion/VS Code).\n* **Immersive Focus Mode**: Instantly collapse the top panels to stretch the AI analysis terminal into a distraction-free, full-page workspace.\n* **Command Palette (`Ctrl + K` or `Cmd + K`)**: Access a high-speed search console from anywhere to search the active student roster, switch workspaces, or toggle Focus mode."
