ing on ensuring consistent state management and proper integration with the component\'s existing structure.\n\n\n**Refining Mouse Up Handler**\n\nI\'m now refining the `handleMouseUp` function, focusing on resetting the drag state. I\'m calculating `deltaX` to check for mouse movement, and I\'m updating the `dragStartRef.current` by setting the `hasMoved` flag based on if the user has moved the mouse. I am also making sure that the style and cursor are properly updated at the end of the action.\n\n\n**Testing Click Conflict**\n\nI\'m now focusing on thoroughly testing the interaction to ensure there are no lingering click interference issues. I\'m verifying the `handleCardClick` function specifically. I\'m checking to see that the `dragStartRef.current.hasMoved` flag is correctly reset after each interaction. I\'m making sure that the click handler properly ignores click events when a drag occurs.\n\n\n**Updating Card Clicks**\n\nI\'m now integrating the `handleCardClick` into the existing logic to manage student selection. I\'m focusing on incorporating `cursor-grab select-none` to prevent accidental text selections, and using `handleCardClick(stud.id, e)` for the selection process. I\'m aiming for smooth interaction within the carousel.\n\n\n**Testing Carousel Completion**\n\nI\'m now focusing on a complete functional test of the carousel, ensuring all aspects function as expected. I\'m verifying responsiveness across devices. I\'m checking that the drag interaction works smoothly in conjunction with card clicks. I\'m also looking for any edge cases I might have missed.\n\nI\'m now confirming the drag functionality works precisely as designed after the click interference. I\'ve re-reviewed code and logic, and I am focusing on making the carousel flawless.\n\n\n**Finalizing Imports and State**\n\nI\'m now integrating the `useRef` hook, adding it to the component\'s import list alongside the existing imports. I\'m focusing on locating references in the horizontal s