  planner_response {
    modified_response: "I have completed the remaining UI polish and refactoring of the Teacher Assistant Platform, thoroughly addressing all styling gaps and feature requests.\n\nHere is a summary of the accomplishments and fixes:\n\n### 1. Unified Theme Colors (Light & Dark Mode)\nI audited the entire application to remove hard-coded UI colors (e.g., rigid \"slate\", \"black\", or specific hex codes that forced components to always look dark). I have refactored all interface views to seamlessly integrate with dynamic CSS variables (such as `surface`, `border-color`, `primary-text`, `elevated`):\n- **RAG Workspace Corrected**: The conversational interface (including panels, chat bubbles, thinking skeleton loaders, and form inputs) will now automatically look clean and illuminated when you switch from dark mod to light mode.\n- **Unified Drawers and Popups**: The details panels for students, materials, and the central `CMD+K` Command Palette all now adopt dynamic backgrounds, effectively dissolving the \"dark mode clash\" under light mode operation.\n\n### 2. Implemented Mouse-Drag Carousels\n- The horizontal student roster carousel along the top of your workspaces now natively supports direct click-and-drag panning via mouse for much quicker and more natural navigation compared to scrollbars!\n\n### 3. Current Platform Features & Actions\nAssuming the back-end connectivity and AI layers were fully activated, here are the full, intended capabilities you can operate across this application:\n- **Global Context Architecture**: Create and switch between dedicated \"Workspaces\" for various classes or subjects (e.g., Geometry 101, Fall Seminar). Each workspace segregates state.\n- **Roster & Performance Tracking**: Maintain individual student profile folders containing metric grades, detailed history notes, specific custom meta fields (like IEP statuses or behavioral cues), and a high-level timeline of academic improvement.\n- **Central Search Navigation**: Launch the `Cmd+K` global command palette anywhere to rapidly index the currently active class workspaces and jump to a student profile without losing context.\n- **Knowledge Base File Manager**: Upload class materials to a local repository pane in the active syllabus context.\n- **AI RAG Assistant (Retrieval Augmented Generation)**: A dedicated dual-pane workspace capable of interpreting multi-layered contextual information. Teachers can \"start a diagnostic\" by feeding subsets of class data (such as purely the Syllabus material or specific students like Aarav and Anna) directly into an AI session, and subsequently chat with the bot to analyze grade regressions and automatically extract interactive \"visualizer\" widgets representing comparative metrics on the fly.\n\n### 4. Technical Answers (Data & Backend Setup)\n- **Hard-Coded Setup State**: Right now in this preview, the initial nested arrays of students, workspaces, grades, and mock-file materials are initialized locally in a structured JavaScript array state block inside `App.tsx` on load; they simulate a fetched response from a server. When you run mutations, we are modifying that temporary localized browser state. \n- **FastAPI Architecture Considerations**: **FastAPI** is an excellent, extremely robust architecture choice for a conversational backend built to coordinate AI model pipelines! If you intend to use heavy RAG retrieval functions, Python\'s data-science ecosystem holds mature indexing tools (e.g., LlamaIndex or LangChain) that seamlessly integrate with FastAPI routes. From there, you could directly attach this React/Vite unified frontend to proxy through an explicit API layer into your Python services."
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
